items.title: Inside LinkedIn’s generative AI cookbook: How it scaled people search to 1.3 billion users
items.summary: LinkedIn is launching its new AI-powered people search this week . It comes a full three years after the launch of ChatGPT and six months after LinkedIn launched its AI job search offering . Deploying generative AI in real enterprise settings is challenging, especially at a scale of 1.3 billion users . LinkedIn had to perfect this on one product before attempting it on another .

items.title: How Deductive AI saved DoorDash 1,000 engineering hours by automating software debugging
items.summary: Deductive AI has raised $7.5 million in seed funding . The company says it's creating a new category of tooling — AI agents that can diagnose production failures in minutes instead of hours . When an incident occurs, multiple AI agents work together to form hypotheses, test them against live system evidence, and converge on a root cause — mimicking the investigative workflow of experienced site reliability engineers .

items.title: MMCTAgent: Enabling multimodal reasoning over large video and image collections
items.summary: MCTAgent enables dynamic multimodal reasoning with iterative planning and reflection . Built on Microsoft’s AutoGen framework, it integrates language, vision, and temporal understanding for complex tasks like long video and image analysis . The post: Enabling multi-video and image reasoning over large video collections was published by Microsoft Research at Microsoft Research .
